functional Programming
    you can pass function as arguments to methods and within those method you can use those functions

    you can write more precise and compact and efficient code

    form java eight onwards, even behavior could be passed US argument, that is, we can pass around
    method functionality and this is possible via lambdas and also something called method references.

    In that sense, from July eight onwards, methods are also considered as first class citizens.

Lmbda
    It is an anonymous function, so it is not an anonymous class, but an anonymous function.

    And it is a compact way of defining a function which can be passed on.

    So it is useful when we want to pass it on some functionality and it helps in doing it in a very compact way